main event: An unidentified object was reported over Davenport, Iowa on April 12, 1965, described as round and silver in color.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 5 seconds before disappearing behind a tower., Two photographs submitted were determined to be artifacts, not depicting any observed object., The report states there was no physical evidence found., The sighting was documented in a Project Blue Book record., The witness did not have the original negative of the photographs.
witness description: Mr. *********, who reported the sighting in a letter dated November 8, 1967.
